  "root_text": {
    "sn11.25:0.1": "Saṁyutta Nikāya 11.25 ",
    "sn11.25:0.2": "3. Tatiyavagga ",
    "sn11.25:0.3": "Akkodhasutta ",
    "sn11.25:1.1": "Evaṁ me sutaṁ—",
    "sn11.25:1.2": "ekaṁ samayaṁ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṁ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme. ",
    "sn11.25:1.3": "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū …pe… bhagavā etadavoca: ",
    "sn11.25:1.4": "“bhūtapubbaṁ, bhikkhave, sakko devānamindo sudhammāyaṁ sabhāyaṁ deve tāvatiṁse anunayamāno tāyaṁ velāyaṁ imaṁ gāthaṁ abhāsi: ",
    "sn11.25:2.1": "‘Mā vo kodho ajjhabhavi, ",
    "sn11.25:2.2": "mā ca kujjhittha kujjhataṁ; ",
    "sn11.25:2.3": "Akkodho avihiṁsā ca, ",
    "sn11.25:2.4": "ariyesu ca paṭipadā; ",
    "sn11.25:2.5": "Atha pāpajanaṁ kodho, ",
    "sn11.25:2.6": "pabbatovābhimaddatī’”ti. ",
    "sn11.25:2.7": "Tatiyo vaggo. ",
    "sn11.25:3.0": "Tassuddānaṁ ",
    "sn11.25:3.1": "Chetvā dubbaṇṇiya māyā, ",
    "sn11.25:3.2": "accayena akodhano; ",
    "sn11.25:3.3": "Desitaṁ buddhaseṭṭhena, ",
    "sn11.25:3.4": "idañhi sakkapañcakanti. ",
    "sn11.25:3.5": "Sakkasaṁyuttaṁ samattaṁ. ",
    "sn11.25:3.6": "Sagāthāvaggo paṭhamo. ",
    "sn11.25:4.0": "Tassuddānaṁ ",
    "sn11.25:4.1": "Devatā devaputto ca, ",
    "sn11.25:4.2": "rājā māro ca bhikkhunī; ",
    "sn11.25:4.3": "Brahmā brāhmaṇa vaṅgīso, ",
    "sn11.25:4.4": "vanayakkhena vāsavoti. ",
    "sn11.25:4.5": "Sagāthāvaggasaṁyuttapāḷi niṭṭhitā. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "sn11.25:0.1": "Linked Discourses 11.25 ",
    "sn11.25:0.2": "Chapter Three ",
    "sn11.25:0.3": "Don’t Be Angry ",
    "sn11.25:1.1": "So I have heard. ",
    "sn11.25:1.2": "At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery. ",
    "sn11.25:1.3": "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants: ",
    "sn11.25:1.4": "“Once upon a time, mendicants, Sakka, lord of gods, guiding the gods of the thirty-three, spoke this verse: ",
    "sn11.25:2.1": "‘Don’t let anger be your master, ",
    "sn11.25:2.2": "don’t get angry at angry people. ",
    "sn11.25:2.3": "Kindness and harmlessness ",
    "sn11.25:2.4": "are always present in the noble ones. ",
    "sn11.25:2.5": "For anger crushes bad people ",
    "sn11.25:2.6": "like a mountain.’” ",
    "sn11.25:2.7": "",
    "sn11.25:3.1": "",
    "sn11.25:3.2": "",
    "sn11.25:3.3": "",
    "sn11.25:3.4": "",
    "sn11.25:3.5": "The Linked Discourses with Sakka are complete. ",
    "sn11.25:3.6": "",
    "sn11.25:4.1": "",
    "sn11.25:4.2": "",
    "sn11.25:4.3": "",
    "sn11.25:4.4": "",
    "sn11.25:4.5": "The Book With Verses is finished. "
  },
